I think that the problem fixed in #191 is that the compressor did not handle a `memoryview`, the compressor required bytes, and depending on where the data came from (maybe another tornado read) it might be a memoryview. So we may need to convert memoryview to bytes before passing it to the compressor, either in `AsyncConn`:

```python
    def send(self, data):
        self.stream.write(self.encoder.encode(data))
```

or maybe just in the compressing encoders e.g. `SnappyEncoder`:

```python
    def encode(data):
        return snappy.StreamCompressor().compress(data)
```

if self.resource is None:
